article.headline: Lipscomb 70, Belmont 60
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Trey Williams scored 16 points and sparked a second-half rally to lead David Lipscomb to a 70-60 win Friday night over city rival Belmont. Host Lipscomb (15-10, 9-5 Atlantic Sun) went on a 17-1 run in the second half, turning a one-point lead into a 58-41 advantage with 5:05 left. Williams scored seven of the 17 points. Belmont (16-9, 10-4 A-Sun) led 33-31 at the half, and its last lead was 39-37 with 12:30 left. Brian Fisk added 15 points for Lipscomb and Eddie Ard also had 15 points and a team-high eight rebounds. Belmont, which shot just 35 percent, had only one player in double figures, Andy Wicke with 17. The Bruins missed 23 of their first 25 second-half field goals. The win gave the Bisons a sweep of the teams' two regular season games. A year ago, Belmont advanced to the NCAA tournament with a win over Lipscomb in the conference tourney championship game. Lipscomb shot 41.4 percent, and made 17-of-20 free throws.
